node.text:
Using everything from fondant to cotton candy, Jackson & Alexandra brought the magic of "Toy Story" to life with their winning cake on this week's episode of "Disney's Magic Bake-Off."

Catch future cake creations every Friday at 8/7c, and watch past clips on @disneychannel and DisneyNOW! 

Decadent Chocolate Cake with Tart Cherry Filling 

Ingredients:

1 sticks butter
1 c water
½  c canola oil
½  c buttermilk
1  t baking soda
2  eggs
2 c flour
2 c sugar
½  t salt
⅓  c cocoa
1  t vanilla
3 c frozen cherries
⅔ c sugar
1 t cornstarch
1 T water
¼ t almond extract

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350

2. In a saucepan combine butter, water, and oil.  Bring to a boil.

3. Remove from heat and let cool

4. In a small bowl combine buttermilk and baking soda. Set aside.

5. In a stand mixer beat eggs.

6. In a large bowl combine flour, sugar, salt, and unsweetened cocoa with a whisk.

7. Add mixture from saucepan to the dry mixture.

8. Add buttermilk, eggs, and vanilla to the large bowl.

9. Whisk together but don't over mix.

10. Pour evenly into 2- 6” pans and 2-8” pans pans.

11. Bake for 25-30 mins

12. Use Food processor and pulse cherries.

13. Add cherries and sugar to a saucepot.

14. In a small bowl make a slurry with water and cornstarch.

15. Add cornstarch to the cherry mixture.

16. Cook over medium heat stirring occasionally

17. When sauce begins to thicken add almond extract

18. Remove from heat and let cool before adding to cake layers

node.title: One bite of this cake will take you to infinity...and beyond!

Bloody Cotton Cocktail

Ingredients:

3 oz blood orange juice
2 oz sour cherry juice
1/2 oz sweet and sour mix
3 oz vodka
1 cup white cotton candy 

Steps:

1. Place about a cup of cotton candy into a martini glass or goblet.

2. Add a cup of ice to a cocktail shaker, then add the blood orange juice, cherry juice, sweet and sour mix and vodka.

3. Shake for about 10 to 15 seconds until chilled.

4. When ready to serve, pour the mixture over the cotton candy and serve immediately.

Black Magic Cocktail

Ingredients:

4 ounces black vodka, or vodka colored with black food coloring
2 oz pomegranate juice
2 oz orange juice
1 oz Luxardo cherry syrup from the jar
1 tsp edible white pearl dust
1 z 151-proof alcohol
Cinnamon

Steps:

1. In the bottom of a shaker, add the black vodka, pomegranate juice, orange juice, Luxardo cherry syrup and pearl dust.

2. Fill the shaker with ice and stir using a bar spoon until chilled, about 10 secs.

3. Strain into a chilled martini glass. Top with 151-proof alcohol and sprinkle with cinnamon for an added effect.

4. Allow flame to extinguish before enjoying.

4. Allow flame to extinguish before enjoying.

Dirty Shirley Shots

Ingredients:

1 ounce grenadine
4 ounces cherry or pomegranate-flavored vodka
4 ounces lemon-lime soda
1 empty syringe (can be purchased at any party store)

Steps:

1. Fill the empty syringe with grenadine. Set aside.

2. Add the vodka and lemon-lime soda to a cocktail shaker filled with ice.

3. Shake gently to combine, about 10 seconds, and strain into a martini glass.

4. Place the syringe into the glass and allow guests to dispense the grenadine into their own drinks upon serving.

1/4 teaspoon pecan flavor
5 cups water, divided
4 teaspoons instant coffee
6 tablespoons agar flakes
1 1/2 cups sugar

Steps:

1. In a small bowl, combine 1/4 cup heavy cream, pumpkin puree and pumpkin pie spice.

2. In another small bowl, combine 1/4 cup heavy cream, maple syrup and pecan flavor.

3. In another small bowl, combine 1/2 cup water and instant coffee.

4. In a large sauce pan, heat 4 1/2 cups water to a boil. Once boiling, add agar flakes and stir until dissolved. Simmer for 3 minutes, then stir in sugar. Divide mixture evenly into three, 3-cup rectangular glass containers.

5. Pour the pumpkin mixture into one glass dish and mix well. Pour the maple pecan mixture into the second glass dish and mix well. In the third glass dish, add the coffee mixture and mix well. Refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight. Before serving, slice jellies into cubes.

6. Serve layered jellies in more coffee with whipped cream.

Ingredients:

1/2 cup milk
1/2 cup water
1 cup all-purpose flour
2 eggs
1/4 teaspoon salt
2 tablespoons butter, melted
1 tablespoon olive oil
3 cloves garlic, minced
3 cups fresh spinach
2 cups chicken breast, cooked and shredded
1 cup mozzarella cheese, shredded
Juice of a lemon
Salt and pepper
2 tablespoons butter
2 tablespoons flour
1 1/4 cups milk, warm
Salt
Freshly ground pepper
1/8 teaspoon nutmeg

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

2. In a blender, add milk, water, flour, eggs, salt and melted butter. Blend until smooth. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.

3. Lightly oil a frying pan with melted butter. Place over medium-high heat.

4. Pour in 1/4 cup batter, and tilt the pan with a circular motion until the batter coats the surface evenly.

5. Cook the crepe for about 2 minutes, until it bubbles up and loosens from the pan. Flip and cook for 2 more minutes on the other side.

6. In a heavy-bottomed pan on medium-high heat, add 1 tablespoon of olive oil.

7. Add garlic and cook until aromatic, about 2 minutes.

8. Add spinach, chicken and mozzarella and cook for 4 minutes.

9. Add lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.

10. Place crepe on a baking sheet or cast-iron pan, place 2 tablespoons of filling in the center and fold up. Repeat with remaining crepes.

11. Pour sauce over the crepes, and broil for 5 to 8 minutes until golden brown.

12. In a heavy-bottomed saucepan, melt butter.

13. Stir in the flour and cook, stirring constantly, until it cooks out, about 2 minutes.

14. Add the warm milk, salt, pepper, and nutmeg, continuing to stir as the sauce thickens.

15. Bring to a boil, then remove from heat.

It's everything you love about Camp Kikiwaka...on a cake! Duo Connor & Emerson dreamed up this "Bunk'd"-inspired masterpiece on this week's episode of "Disney's Magic Bake-Off"

Catch future cake creations every Friday at 8/7c, and watch past clips on @disneychannel and DisneyNOW!

Bunk’d Double Chocolate Chip Cake

INGREDIENTS:

2 c AP Flour
1 c cocoa powder
2 t baking powder
1 ½ t baking powder
¾ t cinnamon
½ t salt
2 c sugar
1 c brown sugar
6 eggs, room temp
½ c coffee
3t vanilla
1 ½ c sour cream
½ c vegetable oil
1 c mini chocolate chips, coat in flour

INSTRUCTIONS:

1. Preheat oven to 325°F

2. In a large bowl whisk together flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, brown sugar, granulated sugar, salt.

3. In a mixer add eggs, coffee, vegetable oil, vanilla extract and sour cream.

4. Add dry mix one cup at a time until well incorporated.
Coat chocolate chips with flour & fold into batter.

5. Prepare 2-6” pans and 2-8” with baking spray & parchment paper circles.

6. Bake cake for 20-30 mins or until a toothpick comes out clean.

7. Once cakes are cooled frost and enjoy.

FROSTING INGREDIENTS:

1 c unsalted butter
2 c powdered sugar
1T vanilla

INSTRUCTIONS:

1. In a clean mixer bowl cream butter and add vanilla until well blended.

2. Add powdered sugar in one cup at a time.

Using everything from fondant to cotton candy, Jackson & Alexandra brought the magic of "Toy Story" to life with their winning cake on this week's episode of "Disney's Magic Bake-Off."

Catch future cake creations every Friday at 8/7c, and watch past clips on @disneychannel and DisneyNOW! 

Decadent Chocolate Cake with Tart Cherry Filling 

Ingredients:

1 sticks butter
1 c water
½  c canola oil
½  c buttermilk
1  t baking soda
2  eggs
2 c flour
2 c sugar
½  t salt
⅓  c cocoa
1  t vanilla
3 c frozen cherries
⅔ c sugar
1 t cornstarch
1 T water
¼ t almond extract

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350

2. In a saucepan combine butter, water, and oil.  Bring to a boil.

3. Remove from heat and let cool

4. In a small bowl combine buttermilk and baking soda. Set aside.

5. In a stand mixer beat eggs.

6. In a large bowl combine flour, sugar, salt, and unsweetened cocoa with a whisk.

7. Add mixture from saucepan to the dry mixture.

8. Add buttermilk, eggs, and vanilla to the large bowl.

9. Whisk together but don't over mix.

10. Pour evenly into 2- 6” pans and 2-8” pans pans.

11. Bake for 25-30 mins

12. Use Food processor and pulse cherries.

13. Add cherries and sugar to a saucepot.

14. In a small bowl make a slurry with water and cornstarch.

15. Add cornstarch to the cherry mixture.

16. Cook over medium heat stirring occasionally

17. When sauce begins to thicken add almond extract

18. Remove from heat and let cool before adding to cake layers

Sorry, but we won't be sharing any of our cheesy potato wedges.

Ingredients:

Potato wedges:
4 1/2 lb whole potatoes
3 tbsp vegetable oil
1 tsp salt
1 tsp paprika
Cheese sauce:
1/3 stick butter
1/3 cup plain flour
2 cups whole milk
2/3 cup sour cream
1 tbsp tomato paste
2 fresh jalapeños, finely chopped
2 cups grated cheese, divided
1/2 tsp salt

Steps:

1. Bring a large pan of salted water to boil.

2. Scrub the potatoes, then cut each into 8 wedges.

3. Cook for 6 minutes, then drain and leave to cool slightly in a colander.

4. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees.

5. Divide the oil between two large baking trays.

6. Add half of the potatoes onto each, then sprinkle the salt and paprika over them.

7. Use a spatula to spread the wedges out and cover each in the oil, salt and spice.

8. Bake for 30 minutes, turning once or twice to allow for even cooking, then leave to cool on the trays.

9. Melt the butter in a large saucepan, then add the flour and stir constantly for 1 minute.

10. Gradually add the milk, whisking thoroughly after each addition to eliminate lumps.

11. Once all of the milk has been added, mix in the sour cream, tomato paste and half of the chopped jalapeños.

12. Once smooth, add half of the cheese and stir until melted before removing from heat.

13. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.

14. Scatter a handful of the remaining grated cheese into the flan dish to help the wedges stay put.

15. Arrange the wedges in a circular pattern in the dish.

16. Pour in the cheese sauce, then top with the remaining cheese and jalapeños.

17. Bake for 15 minutes until warmed through and golden brown on top. Serve immediately.

Bloody Cotton Cocktail

Ingredients:

3 oz blood orange juice
2 oz sour cherry juice
1/2 oz sweet and sour mix
3 oz vodka
1 cup white cotton candy 

Steps:

1. Place about a cup of cotton candy into a martini glass or goblet.

2. Add a cup of ice to a cocktail shaker, then add the blood orange juice, cherry juice, sweet and sour mix and vodka.

3. Shake for about 10 to 15 seconds until chilled.

4. When ready to serve, pour the mixture over the cotton candy and serve immediately.

Black Magic Cocktail

Ingredients:

4 ounces black vodka, or vodka colored with black food coloring
2 oz pomegranate juice
2 oz orange juice
1 oz Luxardo cherry syrup from the jar
1 tsp edible white pearl dust
1 z 151-proof alcohol
Cinnamon

Steps:

1. In the bottom of a shaker, add the black vodka, pomegranate juice, orange juice, Luxardo cherry syrup and pearl dust.

2. Fill the shaker with ice and stir using a bar spoon until chilled, about 10 secs.

3. Strain into a chilled martini glass. Top with 151-proof alcohol and sprinkle with cinnamon for an added effect.

4. Allow flame to extinguish before enjoying.

Ingredients:

1 ounce grenadine
4 ounces cherry or pomegranate-flavored vodka
4 ounces lemon-lime soda
1 empty syringe (can be purchased at any party store)

Steps:

1. Fill the empty syringe with grenadine. Set aside.

2. Add the vodka and lemon-lime soda to a cocktail shaker filled with ice.

3. Shake gently to combine, about 10 seconds, and strain into a martini glass.

4. Place the syringe into the glass and allow guests to dispense the grenadine into their own drinks upon serving.

How do we feel about ramen pizza - smash or pass? 

Ingredients:

2 packs ramen, cooked as instructed
1 large egg, beaten
1/3 cup shredded Parmesan cheese
Cooking oil
2/3 cup pizza sauce
1 1/2 cups mozzarella
6 to 8 slices salami or pepperoni
1 teaspoon dried oregano

Steps:

1. Heat oven to 425 degrees.

2. In a medium bowl, toss the ramen, egg and Parmesan together.

3. In a 10-inch cast-iron skillet, heat some oil over medium heat. Once hot, add the ramen mixture in an even layer and press down with a spatula.

4. Let cook for 1 to 2 minutes. Sprinkle with half of the mozzarella, spread tomato sauce over, then the remaining cheese, top with pepperoni and sprinkle with oregano.

5. Place skillet into the oven and bake for 15 minutes. Slice into wedges and enjoy!

node.text:
Take your homemade brunch to the next level with this bonkers 🍗 & waffles  sandwich.

🎥 : @tastemade_japan

Maple Chicken & Waffle Sandwich

Ingredients:

500g boneless chicken thigh
Oil (to coat waffle maker)
Flour, as needed
Oil for frying, as needed
1 fried egg
Maple syrup, to taste
Marinade:
100g flour
1.5 tsp paprika powder
1 tsp cumin
1 tsp allspice
1 tsp oregano
1 tsp garlic powder
2 tsp salt
2 tsp pepper
200ml milk
Waffle Batter:
150g pancake mix
1 egg
50ml milk
1 tbsp vegetable oil
1 tbsp honey
A pinch of cinnamon powder

Steps:

1. Mix together all the ingredients for the waffle batter.

2. Coat the waffle maker in oil and preheat.

3. Pour the waffle batter into the waffle maker and bake for 5 minutes.

4. In a bowl, combine the ingredients for the marinade and mix well. Dip the chicken thigh and let marinate in the refrigerator for 2 hours.

5. Take the chicken out, coat with flour, and fry in oil at 200°C until golden brown all over. Then, lower the temperature to roughly 160°C and continue to fry until the color of the chicken deepens.

6. Place the fried chicken on top of one waffle and drizzle with maple syrup.

7. Top with fried egg and waffle to complete the sandwich. Enjoy!

Pancake Mix + Hot Dogs = 🤤

🎥: @tastemade_japan 

Ingredients:

1 sausage per hot dog
Pancake Batter:
200g pancake mix
140ml milk
1 egg
Toppings:
Mustard
Ketchup

Steps:

1. Mix together the ingredients for the pancake batter.

2. Pour the batter onto the heated frying pan.

3. Pour the pancake dough in a round shape into a warm frying pan.

4. Place sausage when bubbles appear on the surface as the batter starts to cook.

5. Using spatulas, lift both sides of the pancake and squeeze gently until the pancake is in place.

6. Add a bit of water to the frying pan and cover with a lid. Let steam for about 3 minutes on low heat.

7. Remove from the frying pan and add toppings. Enjoy!
